                            <comment id="13209823" author="stack" created="Thu, 16 Feb 2012 22:32:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mind taking care of this one Doug?  This looks like a 0.92.0ism so needs dnoting so in the book as for 0.92.0.  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13209861" author="dmeil" created="Thu, 16 Feb 2012 23:01:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll take it.  Roger the 0.92-ism.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13210114" author="mspreitz" created="Fri, 17 Feb 2012 07:19:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you saying the current text has been verified as correct for later versions?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13210314" author="stack" created="Fri, 17 Feb 2012 15:14:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Current text is right for older versions I believe.  You are using 0.92 Mike, right?  Its in 0.92 that we need all the extra stuff?  You are using hadoop 1.0.0?  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13210323" author="mspreitz" created="Fri, 17 Feb 2012 15:24:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I tested HBase 0.92.0 with Hadoop 1.0.0.  I doubt this is the only combination for which the current text is deficient.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13446550" author="ivarley" created="Sat, 1 Sep 2012 00:56:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a doc patch that adds this list of client dependency jars.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13446595" author="stack" created="Sat, 1 Sep 2012 04:31:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So, Ian, this is 0.92 or 0.94?  I should call out the hbase version on commit?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13446704" author="ivarley" created="Sat, 1 Sep 2012 13:43:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It was filed in .92, and all of the JARs still seem to be the same in trunk (except the HBase jar). I think it kind of goes without saying that you&apos;d want to use the right HBase JAR for whatever server version you have, but maybe we should expand? In any case, it&apos;s a minor clarification thing so probably not worth a lot of back &amp;amp; forth. If it&apos;s any hassle doing it against 0.92, then just do it in 0.94. And likewise if it&apos;s any hassle doing it against 0.94, just do it in trunk. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13450397" author="stack" created="Fri, 7 Sep 2012 06:12:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to the book (Book needs to be per version.  It isn&apos;t yet).  Thanks for the patch Ian and Mike.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
